.TH "mpvc\-tui" "1" "April, 2026" ""
.SH NAME
mpvc\-tui \- Terminal User Interface for displaying the MPV playlist and
playback
.SH SYNOPSIS
mpvc\-tui options files
.SH DESCRIPTION
mpvc\-tui is a terminal\-based user interface that displays
status/playlist info of the currently mpv instance.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[CR]\-d\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-dir PATH\f[R]
Set the working directory to the specified media directory.
All media operations will be relative to this directory.
.TP
\f[CR]\-h\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-help\f[R]
Display the help message and exit.
.TP
\f[CR]\-H\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-history\f[R]
Start the mpvc\-tui history interface.
This allows you to browse and replay previously played media.
.TP
\f[CR]\-k\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-kill\f[R]
Stop the currently running mpvc\-tui instance.
.TP
\f[CR]\-n\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-notify\f[R]
Enable desktop notifications for mpvc events using notify\-send.
Notifications will appear for playback state changes and media
transitions.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-socket PATH\f[R]
Set the MPV socket path.
Overrides the default socket connection (defaults to MPV\(cqs standard
socket if not specified).
.TP
\f[CR]\-s\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-suggest\f[R]
Suggest a random media item to play based on previously played media.
Useful for discovering content from your history.
.TP
\f[CR]\-S\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-scrobbler\f[R]
Start the mpvc\-tui scrobbler interface.
This feature tracks and logs media that you play.
.TP
\f[CR]\-t\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-tui\f[R]
Start the main TUI for managing the MPV playlist (uses rlwrap for
enhanced readline functionality).
.TP
\f[CR]\-T\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-Tui\f[R]
Combo option that starts mpvc\-tui with both TUI (\-t) and desktop
notifications (\-n) enabled.
This is the recommended starting option.
Additional files provided as arguments will be added to the playlist.
.TP
\f[CR]\-x\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-launch\f[R]
Start mpvc\-tui in a new xterm window.
This respects the \f[CR]$MPVC_TUI_TERM\f[R] environment variable for
terminal selection.
Can be combined with other options.
.TP
\f[CR]\-v\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-version\f[R]
Display the mpvc\-tui version and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
Start TUI with notifications for a media directory
.IP
.EX
mpvc\-tui \-d \(ti/Music \-T
mpvc\-tui \-t
.EE
.PP
Enable desktop notifications separately
.IP
.EX
mpvc\-tui \-n
.EE
.PP
Launch in a new terminal window
.IP
.EX
mpvc\-tui \-x \-t \-d \(ti/Music
.EE
.PP
Access playback history
.IP
.EX
mpvc\-tui \-H
.EE
.PP
Enable media scrobbling
.IP
.EX
mpvc\-tui \-S
.EE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
MPVC_TUI_TERM
Specifies the terminal emulator to use when launching mpvc\-tui with the
\-x option.
If not set, xterm is used as the default.
.TP
MPV_SOCKET
Override the default MPV socket path.
Can also be set directly using the \(ensocket option.
.TP
XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Directory where mpvc configuration is stored.
Defaults to \(ti/.config/ if not set.
.SH FILES
.TP
\(ti/.config/mpvc/mpvc.conf
mpvc\-specific configuration file.
.SH SEE ALSO
mpv(1), mpc(1), mpvc\-fzf(1), mpvc\-web(1), mpvc\-tui(1),
mpvc\-equalizer(1)
